<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/140.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mexican
                                Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-28"><hi rend="italic">November 28,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Transmits a paraphrase of the above telegram of November 26 to the
                            American ambassador, and suggests the negotiation of a treaty for the
                            maintenance of the levee after it is completed.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>